  "body": "``` sol\nimport \"DoesNotExist.sol\"\n```\n\nRunning `truffle compile` with a contract that has an import statement for a file that does not exist reports an obscure error message:\n\n``` sh\nTypeError: Cannot read property 'source' of undefined\n    at include_source_for (/Users/raine/.nvm/versions/node/v5.5.0/lib/node_modules/truffle/lib/contracts.js:90:77)\n    at walk_down (/Users/raine/.nvm/versions/node/v5.5.0/lib/node_modules/truffle/lib/contracts.js:108:9)\n```\n\nI think an easy fix would be to check for the existence of `contract` here:\nhttps://github.com/ConsenSys/truffle/blob/master/lib/contracts.js#L89\n\nThoughts? If this sounds like a good idea, I'm happy to submit a pull request.\n",
